description_more: This field is a summary of the distinct treatment speciality codes a participant has had recorded in their hospital inpatient records. The treatment speciality of the consultant is specialism under which the consultant was working, e.g. cardiology or geriatric medicine, etc.  Note that the original information was obtained from a variety of external sources, some of which used overlapping and contradictory coding schemes. This field has been re-coded to remove such data conflicts.  This field corresponds to the field TRETSPEF_UNI on the HESIN table; see the Inpatient Data Dictionary (~R141140~) in ~L2000~ for information about the HESIN table.  In order to conduct detailed analyses of this data using the source information, researchers will need to gain access to the HESIN table by adding ~F41259~ to their basket.

Method of admission to hospital identifies how a patient was admitted, e.g. an elective admission from a waiting list or an emergency admission, etc.  Note that the original information was obtained from a variety of external sources, some of which used overlapping and contradictory coding schemes. This field has been re-coded to remove such data conflicts.  This field corresponds to the field ADMIMETH_UNI on the HESIN table; see the Inpatient Data Dictionary (~R141140~) in ~L2000~ for information about the HESIN table.  In order to conduct detailed analyses of this data using the source information, researchers will need to gain access to the HESIN table by adding ~F41259~ to their basket.
category: Health-related outcomes > Hospital inpatient > Summary Administration

description_more: This field is a summary of the distinct method of discharge codes a participant has had recorded in their hospital inpatient records. description_more: This field is a summary of the distinct intended management codes a participant has had recorded in their hospital inpatient records. description_more: This field is a summary of the distinct administrative and legal status codes a participant has had recorded in their hospital inpatient records. This field corresponds to the field CATEGORY on the HESIN table; see the Inpatient Data Dictionary (~R141140~) in ~L2000~ for information about the HESIN table.
